Nomura Raises Brazil 2011, 2012 Inflation Estimates, Cuts Selic Forecast

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-09-08T11:45:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/nomura-raises-brazil-2011-2012-inflation-estimates-cuts-selic-forecasts.html
Nomura Securities Co. raised it’s
estimate for Brazilian inflation next year to 6.15 percent from
4.72 percent, analyst  Tony Volpon  said in an e-mailed report.  The bank expects inflation of 6.25 percent this year,
compared with an earlier estimate of 5.87 percent, according to
the report.  Nomura also reduced its forecast for the country’s Selic
benchmark interest rate to 11 percent in 2011 from an earlier
estimate of 12.5 percent. Its forecast for the 2012 Selic rate
fell to 11.5 percent from 12.5 percent.  Nomura adusted its forecast for the real-dollar exchange
rate to 1.65 reais per dollar this year, from an earlier
forecast of 1.57 reais per dollar, according to the report. Next
year, Nomura expects the real to weaken to 1.75 reais per
dollar, compared with an earlier forecast of 1.50 reais per
dollar, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
